Becoming One with the Elements: A Sunday Cold Plunge Reflection

December 29, 2024

Today was nothing short of magical. A day where the elements did not feel like something to battle but to join and become one with. Our weekly Sunday cold plunge began on a rainy, windy beach, where I sat waiting to do Wim Hof breathwork. For many, the weather alone would have been a challenge, but I have come to understand that we are not separate from the earth. Our bodies and this physical human existence are intricately connected to and in coherence with the world around us.

From a 3D perspective, it might seem like we are simply braving the cold and testing our limits, creating a physical experience to challenge beliefs about what is possible. The 3D world ties us to time. It is about showing up, dedicating time, and pushing ourselves to new experiences. But beyond this lies the 4D: the realm of space, the unseen, the connection to the elements and energies that shape our existence.

The earth, water, air, fire, and ether are not just external forces; they are within us, and when we connect with them consciously, they become tools for healing and transformation. Today, I chose to work intentionally with these elements and the four cardinal directions. North, East, South, and West. During the breathwork rounds.

North: Facing Forward with Strength
In the first round of breathwork, I focused on the North, drawing in its healing energy. It represented an opportunity to settle into my body despite the rain and wind, grounding myself in the present moment.

East: Releasing Stagnant Energy
The second round was dedicated to the East and the right side of my body. Here, I became aware of stagnant energy within this part of my being. By focusing my attention, I invited healing light and energy to flow into these areas, allowing tension to dissolve and balance to return.

South: Confronting the Shadows
In the third round, I connected to the South and the posterior side of my body. This brought up feelings of avoidance and fear, disbelief and negativity I had not yet turned to face. Recognizing this, I let go of assumptions and allowed myself to confront these hidden aspects. The release was palpable, as my back muscles relaxed, and my seated posture aligned naturally.

West: Completing the Circle
The final round focused on the West, bringing the journey full circle. This connection was about integrating mind and body, realizing that I was exactly where I was meant to be. Each moment of the day, each challenge, was perfectly designed for me to grow, release, and heal.

The Plunge: Letting Go of Control
After the breathwork, it was time to enter the water. As a community, we stood in a line, linking arms, preparing to immerse ourselves together. While waiting for everyone to be ready, my body began shaking uncontrollably. A neurological response to the cold and my natural desire to remain in control.

This was the hardest part, yet it was also the most transformative. I surrendered to the moment, allowing myself to be one with the experience rather than resisting it. In that surrender, I found peace, merging with the elements instead of being at their mercy.

A Lesson in Awareness and Intention
Today’s experience reminded me of the power of intentionality. Many of us go through life reacting to circumstances, unaware of how connected we are to the earth and its energies. But what if, by consciously working with these forces, we could accelerate our growth and transformation?

We are not separate from the earth. Our bodies are vessels, bridges between the physical and the imaginative, capable of creating and experiencing beyond what we often allow ourselves to believe.

The time to reconnect with this awareness is now. Dive in. Let go of what you think you know, and allow what is to guide you. You owe it to yourself to discover the limitless potential that lies within.


hunter johnson
